        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 8:16AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 816 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Albany, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Us-183 And Us-283, Elbert, Us-
183 Near The Throckmorton-
Baylor County Line, Lusk, Woodson, Throckmorton, The Intersection Of
Us-283 And Ranch Road 209, Us-180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, Fort Griffin, and Albany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
